Fig. 1
 shown the XRD phase and structure of BiOX and N-GQDs/BiOX. As shown in Fig. 1a, the main diffraction peaks of pure BiOBr at 2θ angles of 10.9°, 22.0°, 25.3°, 31.8°, 32.3°, 39.4°, 44.9°, 46.3° and 57.2° are attributed to the reflections of the (001), (002), (101), (102), (110), (112), (004), (200) and (212) crystal planes, respectively, which can match the tetragonal phase of BiOBr (No. 09-0393), while the main diffraction peak of pure BiOCl can match that of BiOCl (No.06-0249) in Fig. 1b. Due to a little amount of N-GQDs and the weak crystal structure of N-GQDs, no diffraction peaks corresponding to N-GQDs are observed in N-GQDs/BiOX composites, suggesting that the compounding of N-GQDs has not affected the crystal structure of BiOX [5,6] (Fig. 2
).
